I also realized you worry less about how the service is going and get to engage with the team.

What are some ways you could be more helpful to your team?

videos.title: Because Of Christ Dual Guitar Instrumental | The Belonging Co
videos.description:
In this video, Nick and Jason get together and created an instrumental version of, Because Of Christ by The Belonging Co.

Why are we doing this?  There are many different ways to utilize an instrumental such as this, but a few ways to do so would be; during a prayer time, or the prayer right before the last song leading into the full version of Because Of Christ (If you have a prayer before the last song), communion would be a great opportunity to play an instrumental like this too.  It also could be fun to play when people are walking into wherever you worship. What we are really wanting is to try and inspire you to not feel like you can't be creative with your team, or feel like you only have to play it like the record always.  We think you and your church will be throughly pleased, maybe surprised, with what the worship team can pull together. Try and have some fun with it! videos.title: Before You Practice...
videos.description:
Do you learn AND practice? Is there a difference?

I think that there is a difference and it took me a very long time to figure that out. I couldn’t remember anything but I practiced for a long time. I didn’t really understand that I wasn’t learning what was in front of me. I learned to play along with the song and I didn’t learn the actual song.

Once I recognized that and I started to go a bit slower in the learning process and then actually practicing, it got so much easier to remember everything for the service. And I ultimately got sooo much better at music.

And often times when I did come up against something that was harder, I’d just figure a different way to play something similar vs taking the time to learn the part.

Learning can be difficult, it takes time to master what you’re trying to learn, so practice as often as you can and I bet you’ll be able to learn to play what you want.

There is time and commitment involved, it isn’t an easy thing sometimes.

What have you been learning and practicing?

videos.title: Quad Cortex or Ampero | Which modeler do you NEED?
videos.description:
This is not a head to head comparison of the two modelers. This is a real world "we only need a few things to get by" comparison.  Jason recently traveled with his Hotone Ampero and really loved using it.  So we figured we'd try to get a close enough sound out of the Quad Cortex and see if you really do need to spend the big bucks on that or go the more inexpensive route with the Ampero.  We thought they both sounded great and honestly if you don't need all the flexibility that the QC offers, we would say save some money and get the Ampero.  It is much more limited in what it can do, but as you hear in this video, it really keeps up.  So do you want to save some money? or no? Nick didn't, he loves having the flexibility and all the DSP power, but that's up to you.
